We took some liberties with the classic French salad Niçoise, but worry not, this
salad is worthy in its own right. Roasted sweet potato marries with traditional
components like tomatoes and green beans for an unexpectedly harmonious medley.
The entire salad is amped up by a creamy lemon-Dijon dressing. Bon appétit!

== Prep ==

Wash and dry all produce oven to 450 degrees. Bring a large #pot of salted water
to a boil. Peel and slice the @Persian cucumber{1}(peeled and sliced into rounds).
Halve, peel, and thinly slice the @red onion{1}(halved, peeled, and thinly sliced).
Peel then slice the @sweet potatoes{12%ounce}(peeled and sliced into 1/4-inch cubes).
Drain and rinse the @chickpeas{1%unit} in a #colander. Finely chop the @parsley{1/4%ounce}(finely chopped). Mince or grate the @garlic{2%clove}(minced or grated). Thinly slice the @chili garlic olives{1%ounce}(thinly sliced). Halve the @lemon{1}(halved). Trim the ends of the @green beans{4%ounce}(trimmed).

== Roast Sweet Potatoes ==

Toss the sweet potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tablespoon}
and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Place in the oven for about
~{20%minutes}, turning halfway through cooking, until golden brown.

== Blanch Green Beans ==

Add the green beans to the boiling water and cook for ~{2-3%minutes}, until
crisp-tender. Drain and rinse under cold water, then cut into 2-inch pieces.

== Lemon-Dijon Dressing ==

In a #large bowl{}, mash 1/4 of the chickpeas until they are smooth. Add the
parsley, @Dijon mustard{1%teaspoon}, the juice of half a lemon, and as much
garlic as you like (start with a little and add more later). Whisk in a large
drizzle of olive oil. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

> Start with a little garlic and add more later. Adjust seasoning to your liking.

== Assemble ==

Arrange the @mixed greens{2%ounce} on a #plate{} and top with the
@grape tomatoes{4%ounce}, sweet potatoes, green beans, cucumbers, olives,
remaining chickpeas, and as much red onion as you like. Season with salt and
pepper.

> You can arrange the ingredients in rows to create a classic Niçoise
presentation!

Drizzle with the lemon-Dijon dressing and dig in!